```javascript
let RngTicker = function(start, end){
    this.start = start;
    this.end = end;
    this.arr = [];
    this.initialize = function(){
        for(let i=this.start; i<=this.end; i++){
            this.arr.push(i);
        }
        //shuffling the array to ensure randomness of sequence
        for(let i=this.arr.length -1; i > 0; i--){
            let j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i+1));
            let temp = this.arr[i];
            this.arr[i] = this.arr[j];
            this.arr[j] = temp;
        }
    };
    this.next = function(){
        if(this.arr.length){
            return this.arr.pop();
        } else {
            return null;
        }
    }
};

let rngTicker = new RngTicker(20, 50);
rngTicker.initialize();
```

The `RngTicker` object maintains an array of integers from start to end. During `initialize()`, it populates the array and shuffles it using the Fisher-Yates algorithm. The `next()` function pops and returns the last element of the shuffled array, ensuring each number is used exactly once. When the array is empty, it returns null.")
